ms and Conditions - Checkout page breaks if you read the terms and\n  conditions.\n* Total shipping value and total price incorrect in transaction results.\n* Total shipping value and total price incorrect in Sales Log details page. (Jun 4th, 2012)\n* Variation sales prices are inaccurate in Product Specials Widget</pre>\n<p>In order to make it easy for you to test 3.8.8.2 before we release it officially, we made the 3.8.8.2-dev package available and you can <a href=\"http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.8.2-dev.zip\">download it from WordPress.org</a>.</p>\n<p>One very important thing though, as the name 3.8.8.2-dev suggests, the purpose of this package is for you to test. It&#8217;s not guaranteed to be stable yet, so please don&#8217;t use this on your live site unless you really know what you&#8217;re doing. This is supposed to be used on your test site only.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s still recommended that you back up your test site before using this package.</p>\n<p>If you discover any new issues introduced by this 3.8.8.2-dev package, please let us know via the comment section below!</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-8-2-dev/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"34\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"Common Gold Cart Questions Answered!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/common-gold-cart-questions-answered/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/common-gold-cart-questions-answered/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 28 May 2012 23:17:08 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Gold Cart\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"WP e-Commerce Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://getshopped.org/?p=270101\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:350:\"&#8220;I have activated my Gold Cart but grid view doesn&#8217;t work it still tells me to purchase the Gold Cart?&#8221; &#8220;I have uploaded multiple images for my product but its only displaying the thumbnail&#8221; &#8220;I Activated Gold Cart but it has no settings?&#8221; &#8220;How can I make my grid view products the same height and [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Mychelle\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5184:\"<ul>\n<li><em><strong>&#8220;I have activated my Gold Cart but grid view doesn&#8217;t work it still tells me to purchase the Gold Cart?&#8221;</strong></em></li>\n<li><em><strong>&#8220;I have uploaded multiple images for my product but its only displaying the thumbnail&#8221;</strong></em></li>\n<li><em><strong>&#8220;I Activated Gold Cart but it has no settings?&#8221;</strong></em></li>\n<li><strong><em>&#8220;How can I make my grid view products the same height and width?&#8221;</em></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Sound familiar? These are the most commonly asked Gold Cart related questions in the Premium Support forum- and often the simplest to answer.  We took some time to remind you about these settings and solutions.  As a reminder, although the <a title=\"link to WP e-Commerce plugin\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/\">WP e-Commerce plugin will always be free in the WordPress repository</a>, the biggest benefit of <a title=\"WP e-Commerce Gold Cart\" href=\"http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/gold-cart-plugin/\">Gold Cart</a> is our one to one <a title=\"Support\" href=\"http://getshopped.org/resources/premium-support/\">support</a>.</p>\n<h2>&#8220;I have activated my Gold Cart but grid view doesn&#8217;t work it still tells me to purchase the Gold Cart?&#8221;</h2>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-270104 alignleft\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" title=\"WP e-Commerce Plugin Purchase options\" src=\"http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Screen-shot-2012-05-28-at-9.51.12-AM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"196\" /><br />\nThe first thing to check here is your API Key. With the Gold Cart plugin you must install and activate the Gold Cart like any WordPress plugin, you must also activate the API Key that was included in your GetShopped purchase receipt.<br />\nTo quickly check if your key is activated (or to activate it) you can visit the store upgrades menu located under the main WordPress Dashboard.<br />\n<strong>Need more info? <a href=\"http://docs.getshopped.org/documentation/activating-your-gold-cart/\">Visit the documentation!</a></strong></p>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><img class=\" wp-image-270105 alignleft\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;\" title=\"WP e-Commerce plugin thumbnail setting\" src=\"http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Screen-shot-2012-05-28-at-9.54.03-AM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"472\" height=\"236\" /></div>\n<h2>&#8220;I have uploaded multiple images for my product but its only displaying the thumbnail?&#8221;</h2>\n<p>&#8220;I Activated Gold Cart but it has no settings?&#8221;So you spent hours uploading images for all your products only to discover that your product page is still only displaying the main product thumbnail image?<br />\nIf you have this problem the first thing you should do is check your presentation settings page located under <em>settings &gt; store &gt;presentation</em>. In the thumbnails section is an option called show gallery or Show Thumbnail Gallery for some of you, this must be turned to yes if you would like your thumbnails to show.</p>\n<p>If your a early supporter of the Gold Cart and think your running an old version you may need to upgrade to make multiple images work with the 3.8 installs of WP e-Commerce. <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/extend/premium-upgrades-files/\">You can upgrade your Gold Cart here</a></p>\n<p>This is another popular question which I think mainly comes from people conditioned to every plugin having its own menu. The current version of Gold Cart (2.9.7) does not have its own menu. Once activated correctly (API Key and plugin activation) the Gold Cart will simply extend on the options already in WP e-Commerce. Most of these settings can be found on the presentation settings page. If you&#8217;re unsure if your Gold Cart is activated the best way to tell is to look at your gateway list, WP e-Commerce should now have ALOT more gateways available for you to use.</p>\n<h2>How can I make my grid view products the same height and width?</h2>\n<p>Gold Cart by default works out the width for each grid item (based on how many across you set) and the height (depending on the length of the title and descriptions). Because each product grid can be a different height some product pages take on a staggered effect. You can get rid of this with some simple CSS.<br />\nYou will want to put this css into your child themes style.css or into your wpsc-default.css sheet if you have moved it into your theme folder.</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">\n.product_grid_display .product_grid_item {\n   width:150px !important;\n   height: 200px !important;\n}\n</pre>\n<p>You will need to adjust the height and width to fit your design however keep in mind that this will be the width and height for all the grid view boxes from now on so make sure you choose a size that will fit with every product you have.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll continue to answer some of our most popular questions about Gold Cart in the coming weeks. If you need help in the meanwhile, log into Premium Support and ask us for personalized help! Our support team is here to help.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/common-gold-cart-questions-answered/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\